			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Michelle Cacho-Negrete</strong></span> writes from her home in a red maple swamp in southern Maine. Her essay in this issue is part of a memoir she&rsquo;s writing about her childhood in New York. Her work has appeared in a number of magazines, and she currently offers writing workshops in both Maine and Italy.</p><a href="/contributors/michelle-cacho-negrete" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
